    "descripcionEs": "La diarrea del viajero es el trastorno de salud mas frecuente entre los viajeros internacionales, afectando al 30-70% de quienes visitan destinos de alto riesgo en paises en desarrollo. Se define como la presencia de tres o mas deposiciones no formadas en 24 horas, acompanadas de al menos un sintoma enterico adicional (calambres abdominales, nauseas, vomitos, fiebre o urgencia fecal). La causa principal es bacteriana en el 80-90% de los casos, siendo Escherichia coli enterotoxigenica (ETEC) el patogeno mas comun a nivel mundial, seguida de E. coli enteroagregativa (EAEC), Campylobacter jejuni (predominante en el sudeste asiatico), Salmonella spp. y Shigella spp. Las causas virales (norovirus, rotavirus) representan el 5-15% de los casos, mientras que los parasitos (Giardia lamblia, Cryptosporidium, Entamoeba histolytica, Cyclospora cayetanensis) causan el 5-10% restante y tienden a producir cuadros mas prolongados. El impacto en el viajero es significativo, con un promedio de 2-3 dias de actividades perdidas o modificadas por episodio.",
    "descripcionEn": "Traveler's diarrhea is the most common health disorder among international travelers, affecting 30-70% of those visiting high-risk destinations in developing countries. It is defined as the occurrence of three or more unformed stools within 24 hours, accompanied by at least one additional enteric symptom (abdominal cramps, nausea, vomiting, fever, or fecal urgency). The primary cause is bacterial in 80-90% of cases, with enterotoxigenic Escherichia coli (ETEC) being the most common pathogen worldwide, followed by enteroaggregative E. coli (EAEC), Campylobacter jejuni (predominant in Southeast Asia), Salmonella spp., and Shigella spp. Viral causes (norovirus, rotavirus) account for 5-15% of cases, while parasites (Giardia lamblia, Cryptosporidium, Entamoeba histolytica, Cyclospora cayetanensis) cause the remaining 5-10% and tend to produce more prolonged illness. The impact on the traveler is significant, with an average of 2-3 days of lost or modified activities per episode.",
